Um, perfectly common, right?

00:01:12.040 --> 00:01:15.559
Um, but there are some simple bottlenecks within this process.

00:01:15.639 --> 00:01:19.199
One is because we can't really anticipate what questions are going to come around,

00:01:19.239 --> 00:01:21.400
come about from that particular delivery.

00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:23.720
Um, there's going to be additional questions.

00:01:23.720 --> 00:01:26.760
And so that means it elongates the time in which we can then

00:01:26.760 --> 00:01:28.720
deliver the particular project.

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:32.879
And it becomes also difficult to then, you know, generate a timeline.

00:01:32.879 --> 00:01:35.800
So timelines will slip and that can have knock-on effects

00:01:35.800 --> 00:01:37.400
to broader project milestones.

00:01:37.440 --> 00:01:39.480
So it's more costly because it costs more time.

