Um, uh, you know, it could be Word.

00:01:49.040 --> 00:01:50.320
It could be Jupyter notebook.

00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:51.480
It could be a variety of things.

00:01:51.480 --> 00:01:51.800
Right.

00:01:52.199 --> 00:01:55.559
Um, but again, this seems kind of innocuous, but there's actually a lot of

00:01:55.559 --> 00:02:00.320
variability within a company, uh, and even between companies on how

00:02:00.320 --> 00:02:01.639
that information is delivered.

00:02:01.720 --> 00:02:05.480
Oftentimes what ends up happening, we converge on the lowest common

00:02:05.480 --> 00:02:10.600
denominator, which is like, let's say emailing a Word document, uh, you know,

00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:13.600
to, to somebody, and so it goes over the wall in that regard.

00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:16.880
Now, data science is a science.

00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:20.440
It's kind of wholly expected that there's going to be questions and

