00:07:58.119 --> 00:08:01.959
So for those that may or may not be familiar, infrastructure as code

00:08:01.959 --> 00:08:05.720
effectively uses a YAML file, which is kind of like this human readable,

00:08:05.920 --> 00:08:10.760
but also a program, pro programmatic way of being able to define resources.

00:08:11.119 --> 00:08:15.000
We would specify a lot of those, um, conditions within our YAML file.

00:08:15.320 --> 00:08:18.200
We now can obviously put this in version control, very important

00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:19.760
to use version control.

00:08:20.239 --> 00:08:23.440
And then we use a CI CD tool, a continuous integration,

00:08:23.440 --> 00:08:24.920
continuous deployment tool.

00:08:25.040 --> 00:08:29.600
In this case called Jenkins to actually set up some of the parameters and then

00:08:29.600 --> 00:08:34.760
using the languages for Terraform and Ansible, uh, both are very, very

00:08:34.760 --> 00:08:36.440
handy little, uh, infrastructures code.

00:08:36.440 --> 00:08:39.840
So for those that may not be familiar, Terraform is helpful for

00:08:39.880 --> 00:08:43.679
establishing very consistent, like, uh, resources in the cloud, whether

00:08:43.679 --> 00:08:48.119
there be AWS or, or Google and Ansible is really helpful for being able

00:08:48.119 --> 00:08:51.960
to configure the software that goes onto those, uh, uh, those resources.

